From b82944cf411fc23a2f6fcec50ef7f33216eacfc5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Subramanian Mohan <subramanian.mohan@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 14:35:19 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] pps: add platform driver for Intel Timed IO (TIO)
 hardware

Add a platform driver to support Intel Timed IO (TIO) hardware
which provides infrastructure for Pulse Per Second (PPS) timing
features available on some Intel platforms.

The driver binds to ACPI enumerated TIO devices and initializes
hardware resources such as the memory mapped register region used
to access the controller.

The platform driver serves as the parent device responsible for
managing the TIO hardware instance and exposing functional blocks
implemented by the controller. To enable modular driver design,
the platform driver registers auxiliary devices using the
auxiliary bus framework. Functional drivers can then bind to
these auxiliary devices independently.

This patch introduces only the core platform driver and the
infrastructure required to expose the hardware blocks. Functional
drivers implementing PPS generation and PPS capture support will
be added in subsequent patches.

The number of TIO hardware instances depends on the platform and
may vary (for example one or two instances). The platform driver
uses a generic design to support multiple instances without
platform specific assumptions.

Co-developed-by: Christopher Hall <christopher.s.hall@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Christopher Hall <christopher.s.hall@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Subramanian Mohan <subramanian.mohan@intel.com>
---
